nd team competitions for the first time since Beijing in 2008 in a sport that used to be known as synchronised swimming.\", \"from\": 381, \"to\": 541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 467, \"end\": 474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.681280791815525e-14, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"USA\", \"from\": 381, \"to\": 384}, {\"ngram\": \"both the duet and team competitions\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 441}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 460}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 493}, {\"ngram\": \"synchronised swimming\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 540}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sport was rebranded eight years ago, after the 2016 Rio Olympics, when the international governing body, World Aquatics, changed the name with a view to increasing visibility and better showcasing the essence of the sport.\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 769, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sport\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 552}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2016 Rio Olympics\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"the international governing body\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 666}, {\"ngram\": \"the name\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 684}, {\"ngram\": \"a view\", \"from\": 690, \"to\": 696}, {\"ngram\": \"visibility\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"the essence\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 768}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Regardless of whether you wish to the call the sport by it's new moniker, or it's more traditional predecessor, you would be hard pushed not to have been impressed by USA's routine which included an incredible underwater moonwalk, while Michael Jackson's Smooth Criminal blaring away in the bac